  "prompt": "What is the chemical formula for Iron III Chloride?",
  "response": "The chemical formula for **Iron(III) chloride** is **FeCl\u2083**.\n\n### Explanation:\n\n- **Iron(III)** indicates that iron has a **+3** oxidation state.\n- **Chloride** has a **-1** charge.\n\nTo balance the charges in the compound:\n- You need three chloride ions (each with a -1 charge) to balance one iron ion with a +3 charge.\n\nThus, the formula is **FeCl\u2083**.\n\n### Structure:\n- **Fe**: Iron\n- **Cl**: Chlorine\n- **FeCl\u2083**: One iron atom bonded to three chlorine atoms\n\n### Uses:\nIron(III) chloride is commonly used as a catalyst in organic synthesis, in water treatment processes to remove impurities, and in the production of other iron compounds.",
